# AGENTS.md mandatory preload

**`AGENTS.md`** is the repository operating contract. Cursor rules mirror it ‚Äî if they diverge, follow **`AGENTS.md`** and fix the rule in the same PR.

## Before every task

1. Read **`AGENTS.md`** before analysis, planning, coding, refactoring, testing, or tool execution.
   - **PRIORITY #1** ‚Äî Drizzle: agents own `db:generate` / `db:migrate:local`; humans do not.
   - **PRIORITY #2** ‚Äî IDE anti-drift: one product name, three layers (`app/` ¬∑ `lib/features/` ¬∑ `components2/`); read surface `*-directory.mdc` before editing.
   - **IDE & AI quickstart** table for fast routing.
   - **¬ß3** for **`pnpm gen`** / Turborepo generators ‚Äî `pnpm gen action --module <slug>` is expanded by **`scripts/turbo-gen.mjs`** (positional `--args`; do not pass `--module` to raw `turbo gen`).
   - **¬ß4** for CI gates and enforcement scripts (including Drizzle migrations when editing `drizzle/` or `lib/db/schema.ts`).
- **¬ß2 ‚Üí E2E playbook** ‚Äî [`docs/testing/e2e-local-playbook.md`](../docs/testing/e2e-local-playbook.md): **never** `pnpm test:e2e` per edit; use `pnpm e2e:preflight:*` + `playwright test -g`.
   - **¬ß5** for routing, auth UX, locale, and `proxy.ts`.
   - **¬ß6** for directory shape, **`lib/` root allowlist (¬ß6.1)**, subtrees (¬ß6.2), and anti-drift (¬ß6.3).
   - **¬ß7** for design system boundaries.
   - **¬ß2 ‚Äî Human approval for FULL commands** ‚Äî agents use L0 only; never `gate:push`, `lint:full`, `knip`, `test:ci`, `build`, or `AFENDA_SKIP_FULL_VERIFY_CONFIRM`.
2. Prefer existing patterns over inventing new structures. Prefer contraction over expansion.
3. Do not introduce new architectural categories, folders, or conventions unless **`AGENTS.md`** is updated first.
4. If user instructions conflict with **`AGENTS.md`**, prefer the safer interpretation and ask for clarification.

## Non-negotiable boundaries

| Boundary | Rule |
|---|---|
| Module public door | `lib/features/<module>/index.ts` only ‚Äî no deep imports across modules |
| ERP business logic | Inside `lib/features/<module>/...` only ‚Äî never in `app/`, `proxy.ts`, or `lib/erp/` |
| `app/` layer | Routing, composition, page wiring only ‚Äî no data/domain implementation |
| Mutations | Server Actions by default; Route Handlers only for `auth`, `cron`, `upload`, `webhooks`, `integrations`, `api/erp/<module>` |
| `proxy.ts` | Session/locale gate only ‚Äî no DB, no business logic, no branching domain rules |
| Banned categories | `services`, `utils`, `helpers`, `repositories`, `controllers` ‚Äî forbidden unless `AGENTS.md` updated first (exception: `lib/utils.ts` per AGENTS ¬ß6.1) |
| `lib/` root | Only AGENTS.md **¬ß6.1** allowlisted `lib/*.ts` files ‚Äî no new loose root files |
| IAM session guards | `#lib/auth` only ‚Äî not `#lib/tenant` |
| Doc accuracy | AGENTS.md paths must match disk in the same PR that moves files |
| Root cleanliness | No dumping directories at repo root or module root |
| UI primitives | **`components/` is hard-deleted.** Shelf: `components2/ui/**` ¬∑ import via **`#components2/ui/*`**. Never recreate repo-root `components/`. |
| Design tokens | `@theme inline` `var(--*)` must resolve to `:root`/`.dark` definitions (`check-design-contract.mjs`) |
| Deleted `components/` | **Entire repo-root `components/` directory is hard-deleted** ‚Äî never mkdir or restore any path under it (`never-restore-deleted-components.mdc`) |
| IDE three-layer drift | **PRIORITY #2** ‚Äî one product name across three layers; no `_SEAL.md` at `lib/features/*` root ¬∑ [ADR-0035](docs/decisions/0035-three-layer-surface-ide-anti-drift.md) |
| Full verify gates | **AGENTS.md ¬ß2** ‚Äî agents MUST NOT run `gate:push`, `lint:full`, `knip`, `test:ci`, `build`, or other full commands; human types `YES`; hook denies agent shells |

## Cross-module import rule

- **Allowed:** `import { X } from "#features/<module>"`
- **Forbidden:** `import { X } from "#features/<module>/data/..."` (outside the same module)
- Same-module relative imports are fine.

## Change governance

- New architectural category ‚Üí update **`AGENTS.md`** first in the same change.
- Conflict with a boundary ‚Üí call it out, explain the risk, propose the closest compliant alternative.
- Treat boundary violations as blockers, not style nits.
